<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="809" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Moffat</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.:]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bluefields</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-08-20"><hi rend="italic">August 20,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Moffat reports that the Madriz forces under Gen. Rivas, numbering
                            700, attacked and were defeated by Mena at Granada; that the attack
                            resulted in complete rout; and that Rivas was killed. Adds that the
                            revolutionaries intend immediate advance upon Masaya.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>